cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

This paper is about using convolutional neural networks for fine-grained semantic segmentation of subdecimeter aerial imagery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new adaptive network structure, which involves learning from the confusion matrix and using a TreeCutting algorithm, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with remote sensing content, which could fall under the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper's focus on aerial imagery suggests that it could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO), which often involves using sensors to perceive the environment.
